The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 30 March is 41,401 (4,791.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 25 March, there were 226 new confirmed cases (26.2 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 18 March, there were 292 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 23% (66 fewer cases).
